test_documentation.description: Evaluates if interactive elements have appropriate focus indicators that meet accessibility standards

tests_performed.name: Focus Outline Presence
tests_performed.description: Checks if interactive elements have a visible focus indicator when receiving keyboard focus
tests_performed.success_criteria: All interactive elements must have a visible outline when focused

tests_performed.name: Focus Outline Offset and Width
tests_performed.description: Evaluates if focus outlines have sufficient width and offset to be visible
tests_performed.success_criteria: Outline offset should be at least 2px; solid outlines should be at least 1px; dotted/dashed outlines should be at least 3px

tests_performed.name: Focus Outline Contrast
tests_performed.description: Measures if focus outlines have sufficient contrast against background colors
tests_performed.success_criteria: Focus outlines should have a contrast ratio of at least 3:1 against adjacent colors

tests_performed.name: Hover Visual Feedback
tests_performed.description: Checks if elements provide sufficient visual feedback on hover
tests_performed.success_criteria: Interactive elements should have a pointer cursor and additional visual changes on hover

tests_performed.name: Focus Outline Obscurement
tests_performed.description: Tests if focus outlines are visible and not obscured by other elements
tests_performed.success_criteria: Focus outlines should not be hidden by other elements on the page

tests_performed.name: Anchor Target Accessibility
tests_performed.description: Verifies if in-page link targets are properly configured for keyboard navigation
tests_performed.success_criteria: Non-interactive elements targeted by in-page links should have tabindex='-1'

test_info.name: Focus Outline Presence
test_info.description: Checks if interactive elements have a visible focus indicator when receiving keyboard focus

documentation.description: Analyzes page for event handling accessibility issues and keyboard navigation patterns

tests.name: Non-interactive elements with event handlers missing tabindex
tests.description: Tests for non-interactive elements (div, span, etc.) that have event handlers but no tabindex attribute. These elements must have tabindex to be keyboard accessible.
tests.impact: Critical - Elements without proper keyboard accessibility cannot be used by keyboard-only users
tests.howToFix: Add tabindex='0' to any non-interactive element that has event handlers

resultsFields.pageFlags.hasMissingTabindex: Boolean flag indicating if issue was found
resultsFields.details.violationCounts.missing-tabindex: Number of elements with this issue
resultsFields.details.events.violations: Array of specific elements with this violation

tests.name: Elements with mouse events but no keyboard events
tests.description: Identifies elements that respond to mouse events (click, hover) but have no keyboard event handlers, making them inaccessible to keyboard users
tests.impact: High - Functionality available only with mouse prevents keyboard-only users from using features
tests.howToFix: Add keyboard event handlers (keydown, keypress) to elements that have mouse handlers

resultsFields.pageFlags.hasMouseOnlyHandlers: Boolean flag indicating if issue was found
resultsFields.details.violationCounts.mouse-only: Number of elements with this issue

tests.name: Modal dialogs without keyboard escape
tests.description: Checks if modal dialogs provide keyboard escape functionality (ESC key)
tests.impact: High - Users may become trapped in modal dialogs without keyboard dismissal option
tests.howToFix: Add a keydown event handler to modal dialogs that closes them on Escape key

resultsFields.pageFlags.hasModalsWithoutEscape: Boolean flag indicating if issue was found
resultsFields.details.violationCounts.modal-without-es: Number of modals with this issue
resultsFields.details.events.summary.modalEscapeSuppor: Information about modals and their escape key support

tests.name: Tab order doesn't follow visual left-to-right order
tests.description: Checks if the tab order of interactive elements follows their visual left-to-right arrangement
tests.impact: Medium - Unpredictable tab order creates confusion for keyboard users
tests.howToFix: Rearrange DOM order or use tabindex to ensure tab order matches visual layout

resultsFields.pageFlags.hasVisualOrderViolations: Boolean flag indicating if issue was found
resultsFields.details.tabOrder.violations: Specific information about tab order violation pairs

tests.name: Tab order doesn't follow visual column order
tests.description: Checks if tab order follows the expected column-based navigation pattern
tests.impact: Medium - Unpredictable tab order between columns creates confusion for keyboard users
tests.howToFix: Adjust DOM order or use tabindex to ensure proper column-based navigation

resultsFields.pageFlags.hasColumnOrderViolations: Boolean flag indicating if issue was found
resultsFields.details.violationCounts.column-order: Number of elements with column order issues
resultsFields.details.tabOrder.violations: Specific information about column order violations

tests.name: Elements with negative tabindex
tests.description: Identifies elements using negative tabindex which removes them from the natural tab order but keeps them focusable programmatically
tests.impact: Medium - Can create accessibility issues if important interactive elements are removed from tab order
tests.howToFix: Replace negative tabindex with tabindex='0' for elements that should be in the normal tab sequence

resultsFields.pageFlags.hasNegativeTabindex: Boolean flag indicating if issue was found
resultsFields.details.violationCounts.negative-tabinde: Number of elements using negative tabindex
resultsFields.details.tabOrder.summary.elementsWithExp: Count of elements with explicit tabindex

tests.name: Elements with unusually high tabindex
tests.description: Identifies elements with tabindex values > 10, which is a poor practice that can create maintenance issues
tests.impact: Low - High tabindex values make tab order harder to manage and maintain
tests.howToFix: Restructure DOM or use smaller sequential tabindex values (preferably 0)

resultsFields.pageFlags.hasHighTabindex: Boolean flag indicating if issue was found
resultsFields.details.violationCounts.high-tabindex: Number of elements with high tabindex values
resultsFields.details.tabOrder.summary.elementsWithExp: Count of elements with explicit tabindex

dataSchema.pageFlags: Top-level flags indicating presence of various issues
dataSchema.details: Detailed information about event handlers and tab order
dataSchema.details.events.handlers: All event handlers categorized by type (mouse, keyboard, etc.)
dataSchema.details.events.violations: Elements with accessibility violations in their event handling
dataSchema.details.tabOrder.tabOrder: All focusable elements in their tab sequence
dataSchema.details.violationCounts: Summary counts of each type of violation
dataSchema.details.violationFlags: Boolean flags for each violation category

testDescription.name: Floating Dialog Accessibility Test
testDescription.purpose: Evaluates floating dialogs and modal windows for accessibility compliance across responsive breakpoints
capabilities: Detects floating dialogs visible on page load
Tests dialogs across all responsive breakpoints
Evaluates content hiding and keyboard accessibility issues
Validates dialog behaviors against WCAG requirements

methodology.overview: This test evaluates floating dialogs across multiple viewport sizes to ensure accessibility in responsive designs
steps: Identify visible floating dialogs (modal windows, cookie notices, etc.)
Detect content overlap and hidden interactive elements
Check for proper headings and structure
methodology.breakpointSelection: Breakpoints are derived from the page's CSS media queries plus standard device sizes

2.4.3.title: Focus Order
2.4.3.description: If a webpage can be navigated sequentially and the navigation sequences affect meaning or operation, focusable components receive focus in an order that preserves meaning and operability.

2.4.7.title: Focus Visible
2.4.7.description: Any keyboard operable user interface has a mode of operation where the keyboard focus indicator is visible.

1.4.13.title: Content on Hover or Focus
1.4.13.description: Where receiving and then removing pointer hover or keyboard focus triggers additional content to become visible and then hidden, the following are true.

2.1.1.title: Keyboard
2.1.1.description: All functionality of the content is operable through a keyboard interface without requiring specific timings for individual keystrokes.

2.1.2.title: No Keyboard Trap
2.1.2.description: If keyboard focus can be moved to a component of the page using a keyboard interface, then focus can be moved away from that component using only a keyboard interface.

4.1.2.title: Name, Role, Value
4.1.2.description: For all user interface components, the name and role can be programmatically determined; states, properties, and values can be programmatically set; and notification of changes to these items is available to user agents.

incorrectHeadingLevel.description: Dialogs should have a proper heading structure starting with a level 2 heading (h2).
incorrectHeadingLevel.impact: Screen reader users rely on heading structure to understand content organization.
incorrectHeadingLevel.remediation: Ensure the dialog has a prominent h2 element or an element with role='heading' and aria-level='2'.

missingCloseButton.description: Dialogs need an accessible close button for keyboard users to dismiss the dialog.
missingCloseButton.impact: Keyboard-only users may become trapped in the dialog with no way to exit.
missingCloseButton.remediation: Add a visible, clearly labeled close button that can be activated by keyboard.

improperFocusManagement.description: When a dialog is closed, focus should return to an appropriate element, typically the element that opened the dialog or a logical location in the page.
improperFocusManagement.impact: Screen reader and keyboard users may lose their place in the page when dialogs are closed.
improperFocusManagement.remediation: Implement proper focus management by moving focus to a logical element (usually at the top of the page) when the dialog closes.

hiddenInteractiveContent.description: Interactive elements should not be obscured by floating dialogs as they become inaccessible.
hiddenInteractiveContent.impact: Users cannot interact with obscured elements, breaking functionality of the page.
hiddenInteractiveContent.remediation: Ensure dialogs don't overlap interactive elements, or make the dialog modal with proper focus management.

contentOverlap.description: Dialogs overlap with non-interactive page content.
contentOverlap.impact: Visual content may be hidden from users, though functionality is not affected.
contentOverlap.remediation: Implement modal dialogs that separate dialog content from page content, or position floating elements to minimize content overlap.

fieldDefinitions.breakpoints: Array of viewport widths (in pixels) tested during the analysis

consolidated.description: Aggregated results across all tested breakpoints

summary.uniqueDialogs: Number of distinct floating dialogs found on the page
summary.totalIssues: Total number of accessibility issues found
summary.criticalIssues: Number of critical severity issues that directly impact usability
summary.moderateIssues: Number of moderate severity issues that may affect some users

consolidated.issuesByType: Issues organized by type and severity with affected elements

closeButtonAnalysis.description: Analysis of dialog close buttons and their focus management

fields.hasCloseButton: Whether a close button was found in the dialog
fields.closeButtons: List of close buttons with their properties

focusManagement.description: Analysis of where focus moves when the dialog closes

fields.analyzed: Whether focus management could be analyzed
fields.hasEventListeners: Whether the button has detectable event handlers
fields.willMoveFocus: Whether focus will likely move when the dialog closes
fields.targetIsValid: Whether the focus target is a valid accessible element
fields.focusViolation: Whether a focus management violation was detected
fields.violationReason: Description of the focus management issue

fields.hasCommonTrapClasses: Whether the dialog has classes that suggest a focus trap
fields.hasTrapElements: Whether the dialog has elements that implement a focus trap
fields.likelyHasFocusTrap: Whether the dialog likely implements a focus trap based on the above

Ensure all dialog content is accessible via keyboard navigation
